This paper is primarily focused on information retrieval (IR) and learning to rank (LTR), which are core topics in the cs.IR sub-category. The use of deep neural networks and attention mechanisms also suggests a connection to the cs.LG sub-category, which deals with machine learning and deep learning. Additionally, the use of embeddings and natural language processing techniques suggests a connection to the cs.CL sub-category, which deals with computational linguistics. The application of the model to image retrieval data sets suggests a connection to the cs.CV sub-category, which deals with computer vision. Finally, the use of a decoder mechanism to learn the ranks of search results suggests a connection to the cs.AI sub-category, which deals with artificial intelligence and machine learning.
